<setup>

    <math name="a"><selectFromSequence from="-4" to="4" step="1" exclude="0 1 -1"/></math>
    <math name="b"><selectFromSequence from="-4" to="4" step="1" exclude="0 1 -1 $a"/></math>
      <math name="c"><selectFromSequence from="-4" to="4" step="1" exclude="0 1 -1"/></math>
    <math name="k">$c*pi/12</math>
    <function name="f" symbolic="false" >
      $a*sin(x)+$b*cos(x) 
    </function>  
    <derivative name="fP"> $f </derivative>
</setup>

<p>
  Let <m>f(x) = $f</m> and suppose that <m>a = <math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math></m>.  Use the given formula and <m>a</m>-value to respond to the following prompts.
</p>

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>
        Use appropriate shortcut rules to find a formula for <m>f'(x)</m>.
      </p>
      <p><m>f'(x) = </m>     
        <answer>
          <award>$fP</award>
        </answer>
      </p>  
    </li> 
    <li>
      <p>
        State the exact values of <m>f(<math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math>)</m> and <m>f'(<math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math>)</m>.
      </p>
      <p><m>f(<math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math>) = </m>     
        <answer>
          <award>$$f($k)</award>
        </answer>
      </p>
      <p><m>f'(<math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math>) = </m>     
        <answer>
          <award>$$fP($k)</award>
        </answer>
      </p>  
    </li> 
    <li>
      <p>
        State a formula for <m>L(x)</m>, the tangent line approximation to <m>f</m> at <m>x=<math simplify>$c/12 * pi</math></m>.
      </p>
      <p><m>L(x) = </m>     
        <answer allowedErrorInNumbers="0.01" allowedErrorIsAbsolute>
          <award>$$f($k)+$$fP($k)(x-$k)</award>
        </answer>
      </p> 
    </li> 
  </ol>
</p>  
  